Patch Set 3:

> It still crashes when the dialog box is closed.

Well of course it does.. didn't yet write anything about it yet. When you close the dialog, the thread with the tests is still running, however you destroy the whole class in the main thread. Welcome to the multi-threaded world.  

So before you exit the dialog, you have to stop the thread, but you can't really do that. So what you have to do instead is signal to the thread that it should stop (just set a std::atomic variable or guarded variable with std::mutex) and in the thread, check the variable in-between tests (if true, gracefully return from the thread function, which will stop the thread). 

In the main-thread then just use std::thread::join - so the main thread will wait for the thread to finish.  

This should prevent a crash...
